Belly Dance EvolutionHello, my name is Michael Turkic from interCulture management, and along with Jrisi Jusakos, we aim to bring BELLYDANCE EVOLUTION to Australia in March 2014. Devised by the world's most recognised Belly Dance exponent, Jillina, BELLYDANCE EVOLUTION combines the ancient dance styles of the Middle East, with contemporary theatre design and production.Of our $16,000 budget we need:*   $5000 for marketing, web and print advertising including:*   Newspaper adverts in Middle East press, and*   TV Placement*   Web AdvertisingWhy do we need this?Because this troupe is sourced from LOS ANGELES and we have funding in place for travel and accommodation.The Good StuffThere is very little culturally specific entertainment in Australia for those of Middle Eastern heritage. Australia has a vibrant and active community drawn mostly from Lebanon, Iraq, Iran, and other Middle Eastern countries, mainly centred around Western Sydney. BELLYDANCE EVOLUTION would provide:
A Major cultural experience for the community, and;
The chance for Anglo Australian's to join with the Middle Eastern community in a positive way by sharing some of their culture, and;
Provide young artists the chance to work in masterclasses with Jillina and her company
Other Ways You Can HelpHelp us by contributing directly or telling other's about this wonderful production and enterpriseYou can find out more by visiting Hathor Dance Studio:http://www.hathordancestudio.com.au/And that’s all there is to it.
